    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "t_start": 0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Put a million spins in a magnetic field. They all start pointing the same direction. Wait a moment \u2014 they fan out into a smeared mess and their combined signal vanishes.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.46,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B01.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "t_start": 9,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Apply one carefully timed pulse. The fan reverses. At exactly twice the wait, every spin snaps back into step \u2014 and the signal returns from nothing. That is the spin echo.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.83,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "THE QUESTION",
      "t_start": 18,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "How does one flip pulse undo what randomness started \u2014 and why does the echo arrive at exactly twice the wait time?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "card",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "How does one flip pulse undo what randomness started \u2014 and\u2026",
            "eyebrow": "THE QUESTION",
            "topic": "QUANTUM MECHANICS"
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B03.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "QUANTUM MECHANICS",
        "headline": "Spins fan out, signal dies.\nOne \u03c0-pulse: signal returns at 2\u03c4.",
        "dek": "The spin echo: time-reversing inhomogeneous dephasing"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.4,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "t_start": 27,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "In a real magnet the field is not perfectly uniform. Each spin sees a slightly different field and precesses at a slightly different rate \u2014 faster or slower than the mean.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.87,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "t_start": 38,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The fast spins run ahead; the slow ones fall behind. After time tau the fan has spread over 360 degrees. The total magnetization averages to zero \u2014 the signal dies.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.55,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "t_start": 48,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "A pi-pulse flips every spin \u2014 it mirrors them across the equator. The spin that was 30 degrees ahead is now 30 degrees behind. The one that was behind is now ahead. Their ordering is reversed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.54,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "t_start": 60,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "After the flip, the fast spins are still fast \u2014 but they are now behind. They chase the slow ones. After exactly another tau, everyone arrives at the same point. Echo.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.06,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "t_start": 71,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The echo amplitude decays as e to the minus 2 tau over T2 \u2014 only from real spin-spin interactions that are not time-reversible. Static field errors cancel exactly.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.0,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "t_start": 81,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "This is why MRI works in an imperfect magnet. Vary tau, measure echo heights, fit the decay \u2014 you get T2 from a machine whose field is uneven by one part in a million.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.68,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "t_start": 91,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Illustrative: tau equals 50 ms. Echo amplitudes at 50, 100, 200 ms are 0.85, 0.72, 0.52 of maximum. Fitting e to the minus 2 tau over T2 gives T2 approximately 360 milliseconds.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "manim",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 18.63,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-spin-echo/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-spin-echo/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "RECAP",
      "t_start": 103,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The spins dispersed because they precessed at different rates. A pi-pulse reversed who was ahead. After another wait the same length, they realigned. Time reversed \u2014 at 2 tau.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "card",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
